  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PO4-2 Plant Lake Water Management: from algae pollution to PO4 reuse in support of local agriculture</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Short general project overviewLG Sonic has developed an easy, economically attractive and environmentally friendly manner to bind phosphorous (P) in a highly pure form from lake water. This P can be directly used as fertilizer in surrounding agricultural areas. This system makes use of an innovative method to filter one layer of the water only, specifically the layer where P accumulates during summer months when the lake stratifies. Thanks to this method, the water can be treated without adding a metal or chemical to the water that may negatively affect the ecosystem.The envisioned project aims at providing a solution based on the PO42Plant technology of LG Sonic for Lake Qaraoun. To do so, LG Sonic collaborates with the Litani River Authority and Waternet to define the technological and economic feasibility of this technology for Lake Qaraoun. This is because the feasibility of the PO42Plant depends on many factors that need to be addressed, such as the concentration of P in the lake; the level of stratification; the facilities around the lake to implement the technology and the possibility to use the recovered P as fertilizer.&#x2022;	Initial activities and results of the projectAfter a successful feasibility study in the PO4-2-Plant project, LG Sonic and Wereld Waternet will be able to implement the PO4-2-Plant technology in Lake Qaraoun. This will improve the local situation in the Bekaa valley two-fold:1. Restore the water quality in Lake Qaraoun and prevent HABs, making it possible for farmers and fishers to use the lake water once more for irrigation, fishing and recreational activities.2. Provide local farmers with low cost, sustainable fertilizer for their farmland, isolated from Lake Qaraoun, contributing to a circular economy.</narrative>
  </description>
